  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" Shubhkaran Singh versus Abhayraj Singh & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_6_601_606','2025INSC628'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SHUBHKARAN SINGH<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>ABHAYRAJ SINGH & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 6 S.C.R. 601</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 628</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002132025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the petition filed by the petitioner herein u/Or.18 Rule 17, Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 was rightly rejected by the High Court. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 &ndash; Or.18, r.17 &ndash; Court may recall and examine witness &ndash; Power under the petition filed by the petitioner u/Or.18, r.17 &ndash; Correctness: Held: Power to recall and re-examine a witness is exclusively that of the court trying the suit &ndash; Parties to the suit cannot take any objection to the question asked nor can they be permitted to cross-examine any<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 04-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> SPECIAL LEAVE PETITION (CIVIL) No. 12012/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_6_601_606','2025INSC628','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_6_601_606',